RIFTSMUD ADMIN WIZARD HANDBOOK

WHO THIS IS FOR
Head administrators and co-admins with final authority over staff,
players, and server operations.

POSITION AND ROLE
  position: arch or head arch
  wiz_role: admin (synced automatically from position)

TOOLS YOU MUST HOLD
All five staff objects are granted on promotion and relog if missing:
  Staff of Demotion   promote, demote
  Staff of Domains    domain
  Staff of Creation   create, modify, add, delete, about, more (QCS),
                      plus clone, purge
  RP Skill Tool       tool, rptool
  Tattoo Gun          inscribe

COMMAND ACCESS
Admin wizards get the full admin and creator command paths, including:
  update, eval, clone, dest, stat, snoop, invis, trans, goto
  warmboot, rid, setrole, xmote, playerwipe, force, and related adm cmds
All wizards also get ambassador file-editing commands (ed, cat, ls, cd, etc.)
and workroom.

QCS still requires the staff of creation in inventory even for admins.

STAFF MANAGEMENT (setrole)
The canonical command to change an online wizard's role:
  setrole <player> <admin|domain|coding|rp>
One line: use setrole for staff role changes; it updates position and
syncs wiz_role automatically.
You do not need the Staff of Demotion in hand to run setrole.
Mapping: admin->arch, domain->domain_wiz, coding->creator, rp->rp_wiz
Target must already be a wizard and online. For mortals, promote first.

PROMOTION AND DEMOTION
Use the Staff of Demotion (promote or demote) for menu-based tasks and
promoting mortals to wizard:
  Option 1 - Promote to: arch, domain_wiz, creator, or rp_wiz
  Option 2 - Demote wizard to mortal (clears tools and role tag)
Or use xmote for offline position changes (admin only).

Position is the source of truth. wiz_role tags update automatically.

DIRECTORY ACCESS
  Player saves: /secure/save/users/<letter>/<name>.o
  World content: /domains/ (game areas, e.g. Praxis)
  Staff realms: /realms/<name>/area/ (per-wizard QCS sandboxes)
  Wiz tools: /domains/adm/wiz_tools/
  Logs: /log/adm/ for staff actions

YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES
  Final staff decisions: promote, demote, boot, wipe (rid)
  Server maintenance: warmboot, shutdown, daemon reload via staff menu
  Resolve escalations from Domain, Coding, and RP wizards
  Grant domain access when domain staff grant/revoke needs backing

NOT YOUR JOB ALONE
  Day-to-day area building (assign to Coding wizards)
  Routine skill and tattoo requests (assign to RP wizards)
  Domain directory housekeeping (assign to Domain wizards)

SERVER NOTES
  warmboot reloads domain, daemon, and cmd files only.
  It does NOT reload std/user.c, living.c, room.c, armour.c, or combat.c.
  Those require ./mud.sh stop && ./mud.sh start from the shell.

